WEBVTT

00:15.750 --> 00:16.625
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:16.709 --> 00:19.000
-Ah. Thank you, Matilda.
-My pleasure.

00:19.083 --> 00:20.625
-CUSTOMER: Hey, look out!
-(WOMAN SCREAMS)

00:21.000 --> 00:22.083
(GLASS SHATTERS)

00:24.291 --> 00:26.750
Jacinto Salas,
he's gonna kill you.

00:27.041 --> 00:30.083
Either way, you won't be around
to hear about it.

00:30.917 --> 00:31.917
JUNIOR: What happened?

00:32.208 --> 00:34.542
That little shit Salas
just took a swing at me.

00:35.083 --> 00:36.583
We're gonna hit him back.

00:41.166 --> 00:43.625
FRANK SWEENEY: Put me out
of my misery.  (CHOKING)

00:44.250 --> 00:45.375
JETT: You're gonna pay Neil...

00:45.709 --> 00:47.417
and get him
the fuck away from you.

00:47.500 --> 00:49.083
(SIGHS) I'm free.

00:50.125 --> 00:51.291
I don't want you workin'.

00:51.792 --> 00:52.959
What's that supposed to mean?

00:53.792 --> 00:55.500
JUNIOR: When you're with me,
you don't need to work.

00:56.125 --> 00:57.208
MAN:
You're stalkin' her.

00:57.458 --> 00:58.709
BENNIE: Just wanna make sure
she's okay.

00:58.917 --> 01:00.250
MAN: She's gonna recognize
your voice.

01:00.333 --> 01:02.041
She's gonna recognize
your face.

01:02.125 --> 01:03.625
You're gonna get busted.

01:17.834 --> 01:19.500
(record player clicks)

01:25.208 --> 01:28.458
("Save Me"
by Nina Simone playing)

01:32.834 --> 01:36.500
♪ Save me ♪

01:39.000 --> 01:42.166
♪ Somebody save me ♪

01:44.000 --> 01:47.417
♪ Save me ♪

01:47.500 --> 01:49.375
♪ Somebody save me ♪

01:51.333 --> 01:56.917
♪ I promised myself
after the last romance ♪

01:57.000 --> 02:00.291
♪ That I wouldn't give it
a second chance ♪

02:00.375 --> 02:03.375
♪ They say if you seek
you're sure to find ♪

02:03.458 --> 02:06.417
♪ And I know how
true that is ♪

02:06.500 --> 02:09.333
♪ 'Cause the closer
I get to you, baby ♪

02:09.417 --> 02:11.959
♪ Yeah, you driving me ♪

02:12.041 --> 02:14.375
♪ Clean out of my mind ♪

02:14.458 --> 02:18.125
♪ I said save me ♪

02:18.208 --> 02:22.041
♪ Somebody save me ♪

02:22.125 --> 02:25.875
♪ Anybody save me ♪

02:25.959 --> 02:30.875
♪ Somebody save me ♪

02:30.959 --> 02:35.083
♪ Those who love
always give the most ♪

02:35.166 --> 02:39.125
♪ We're crying together
from coast-to-coast ♪

02:39.208 --> 02:43.250
♪ 'Cause love makes me
cold and hurt inside ♪

02:43.333 --> 02:45.917
♪ These tears of ours
unjustified ♪

02:46.000 --> 02:47.625
♪ I'm begging you to save me ♪

02:47.709 --> 02:50.750
♪ Hang on, somebody save me ♪

02:52.291 --> 02:53.709
(scatting)

02:56.500 --> 02:57.333
(elevator dings)

02:57.417 --> 03:00.542
♪ ♪

03:08.166 --> 03:12.625
♪ Those who love
always give the most ♪

03:12.709 --> 03:16.166
♪ We're crying together
from coast-to-coast, oh! ♪

03:16.250 --> 03:17.917
(song ends abruptly)

03:18.375 --> 03:19.834
Bennie, Carl.

03:19.917 --> 03:22.166
Bennie:
Jett, he'll be just a minute.
Have a seat.

03:22.250 --> 03:23.667
You know, I can come back
some other time.

03:23.750 --> 03:25.834
-I mean, if he's busy.
-You're funny.

03:25.917 --> 03:27.000
(chuckles)

03:27.083 --> 03:30.041
-Can I take your coat?
-Who's funny now?

03:30.125 --> 03:31.375
He'll be just a minute.

03:31.458 --> 03:33.417
I heard.
Who's Blondie outside?

03:33.500 --> 03:35.583
-He bother you, honey?
-I hate to say it,

03:35.667 --> 03:37.041
but he doesn't seem to know
what he's doing.

03:37.125 --> 03:38.458
Yeah, he's a real "pro."

03:38.542 --> 03:40.083
Yeah, he's not on
the same page we are.

03:40.166 --> 03:41.542
Carl:
He's a page ahead of us.

03:41.625 --> 03:43.417
-Man: I saw it
in a dream recently.
-Charlie: Ah.

03:43.500 --> 03:47.000
Man:
And I knew, right away,
that I would be there again.

03:47.083 --> 03:49.834
Uh, Viktor, meet
my dear friend, Jett.

03:51.959 --> 03:54.000
Pleasure to meet you,
Jett.

03:54.083 --> 03:55.834
Sorry if I kept
your friend.

03:55.917 --> 03:59.458
No apology necessary.
I'm sorry to interrupt.

04:00.792 --> 04:02.834
Do you like
coin tricks, Jett?

04:03.709 --> 04:05.542
Never really thought
much about them.

04:05.625 --> 04:07.208
A disappearing
coin trick

04:07.291 --> 04:10.709
is basically a trick
that says now you see it,

04:10.792 --> 04:12.542
now you don't.

04:12.625 --> 04:16.000
You are the same thing,
but in reverse.

04:16.083 --> 04:18.458
Now that you are here,

04:18.542 --> 04:20.375
you cannot be unseen.

04:20.458 --> 04:22.625
You've used that before.

04:22.709 --> 04:24.834
(chuckles)

04:26.750 --> 04:28.333
Take care, Jett.

04:30.250 --> 04:32.166
(sighs)

04:35.750 --> 04:39.000
("Save Me"
by Nina Simone playing)

04:43.291 --> 04:46.959
♪ Save me ♪

04:50.750 --> 04:52.834
Hot damn, Jett.

04:52.917 --> 04:55.291
You make me want
to start smoking again.

04:55.375 --> 04:57.500
So, smoke.

04:57.583 --> 04:59.542
I won't tell.

04:59.625 --> 05:01.041
♪ Somebody save me ♪

05:02.041 --> 05:04.625
♪ I promised myself after... ♪

05:04.709 --> 05:06.166
(song ends abruptly)

05:07.709 --> 05:10.875
(traffic whooshing)

05:16.917 --> 05:19.417
(clattering)

05:37.250 --> 05:39.417
♪ ♪

05:43.125 --> 05:45.000
Where the fuck have
you been? Huh?

05:45.083 --> 05:47.709
-What the fuck?
Get your hands off me!
-Fucking cow!

05:47.792 --> 05:50.834
Aah, stop hitting me
you little prick!

05:50.917 --> 05:54.250
-(grunting, yelling)
-Ow, ow, ow! My arm is broken!

05:54.333 --> 05:56.291
Did you do this?

05:56.917 --> 05:58.166
You did this,
didn't you?

05:58.250 --> 06:00.000
Well, you walked out on me!
What did you expect?

06:00.083 --> 06:03.542
Not for you to fuck my place up!
Why would I expect that?

06:03.625 --> 06:06.166
Those guys messed me up.

06:06.250 --> 06:08.208
The rich kid teenagers
messed you up?

06:08.291 --> 06:11.125
The one fuckhead's uncle is
some Argentinian gangster!

06:11.208 --> 06:13.834
He sent some gorilla,
he almost broke my fingers!

06:13.917 --> 06:15.583
Why'd he stop?

06:15.667 --> 06:18.208
Look, I'm done.

06:18.291 --> 06:19.583
I'm out.

06:19.667 --> 06:23.000
And I never want to see your
dickwad face ever again.

06:25.709 --> 06:27.000
Where did you steal this?

06:27.083 --> 06:29.500
-Are you listening to me?
-Are these bills marked?

06:29.583 --> 06:31.667
You're mentally ill,
Neal!

06:31.750 --> 06:33.959
We're square,
now leave!

06:35.792 --> 06:38.375
Those guys are gonna want
interest on the initial loan.

06:38.458 --> 06:40.542
I added a thousand
on top for that.

06:40.625 --> 06:42.792
(panting)

06:44.917 --> 06:48.667
Why-why we've gotten into this
adversary relationship here,

06:48.750 --> 06:50.625
I-I... don't know.

06:50.709 --> 06:53.417
Look,
it's like I said.

06:54.750 --> 06:58.208
You get your sorry ass out
of my sight, okay? Forever.

06:58.291 --> 06:59.333
(box thuds)

06:59.417 --> 07:01.041
We're blood.

07:01.125 --> 07:03.500
I-I'm the only one
who's ever had your back.

07:03.583 --> 07:05.125
(scoffs)

07:05.208 --> 07:07.667
-How?
-Seriously?

07:07.750 --> 07:09.458
Do you have
the slightest idea

07:09.542 --> 07:11.250
how stupid you
sound right now?

07:11.333 --> 07:13.750
You think I enjoy my sister
splayed out on a mattress,

07:13.834 --> 07:15.375
some douchebag
cumming on your tits?

07:15.458 --> 07:17.959
Divided by the number of fucks
I give about what you think,

07:18.041 --> 07:19.667
it comes down
to triple zero.

07:19.750 --> 07:21.208
It killed me.

07:21.291 --> 07:23.208
But you came to me,
remember?

07:23.291 --> 07:26.250
-It doesn't matter--
-You came to me, and I helped
you fix your problem for you.

07:26.333 --> 07:29.083
So now, if some
kind of wild hairs
springing up your ass

07:29.166 --> 07:31.834
-are making you go all amnesia--
-Either way, Neal, I'm out!

07:31.917 --> 07:34.792
Besides, don't-don't
pretend with me.

07:34.875 --> 07:36.208
You like it.

07:36.291 --> 07:37.792
I'm not saying
it's your true calling,

07:37.875 --> 07:39.959
but a part of you likes
making money this way.

07:40.041 --> 07:41.583
I don't really need
all this perspective, okay?

07:41.667 --> 07:43.583
-Just fucking leave.
-I don't blame you.

07:43.667 --> 07:45.792
You're naturally good at it.
You always were.

07:45.875 --> 07:48.583
(panting):
You remember, uh,

07:48.667 --> 07:50.667
Esperanza Beach?

07:52.208 --> 07:53.542
-(cracks)
-(Neal shrieks)

07:54.083 --> 07:56.667
(grunts, panting)

07:56.750 --> 07:58.250
You bitch!

07:58.333 --> 08:00.458
You broke my nose!

08:01.041 --> 08:03.542
Charlie:
Do you know what I appreciate
about you the most?

08:03.625 --> 08:04.709
Jett:
Trick question.

08:04.792 --> 08:06.625
Charlie:
You're not
a herd animal.

08:06.709 --> 08:08.542
So many women I know,
even the smart ones,

08:08.625 --> 08:10.291
they like
being in packs,

08:10.375 --> 08:11.959
doing the same thing,
the same way,

08:12.041 --> 08:16.000
and then checking in
with each other to discuss
every detail.

08:17.125 --> 08:19.709
You aren't built
that way. (smacks lips)

08:19.792 --> 08:22.208
You know
why that is?

08:22.291 --> 08:24.417
-I don't know.
-(chuckles)

08:24.917 --> 08:28.125
You think, uh, it was
your upbringing or what?

08:28.208 --> 08:30.875
-Never really thought about it.
-Hmm.

08:32.959 --> 08:35.208
What were you like
as a kid?

08:36.375 --> 08:38.458
Maybe we should listen to this
one more time.

08:45.417 --> 08:48.667
In a nutshell,
don't ask me any
personal questions.

08:48.750 --> 08:50.542
Jett:
No, in a nutshell,

08:50.625 --> 08:52.417
I'm just getting warmed up.

08:52.500 --> 08:55.000
("Save Me"
by Nina Simone playing)

08:55.083 --> 08:57.375
You gonna tell me
how you really got hurt?

08:57.458 --> 09:00.000
Or you gonna keep pretending
you had a mole removed?

09:00.083 --> 09:02.333
If I did, you'd
never believe it.

09:02.417 --> 09:04.667
Try me.

09:07.250 --> 09:09.792
You ever go through periods
where you sleepwalk?

09:10.458 --> 09:12.041
No.

09:12.125 --> 09:12.875
♪ Save me... ♪

09:12.959 --> 09:14.750
Well, this isn't
exactly something

09:14.834 --> 09:16.417
I go around
admitting, but...

09:16.500 --> 09:19.291
when I was little,
I guess I just, uh,

09:19.375 --> 09:20.709
I don't know, I guess I'd just

09:20.792 --> 09:23.125
leave my bedroom and go looking
for the bathroom,

09:23.208 --> 09:25.417
and end up outside in the yard,

09:25.500 --> 09:27.375
like, staring at a tree.

09:27.458 --> 09:29.500
That's where my grandma
would find me.

09:29.583 --> 09:32.041
-Mm-hmm.
-So now,

09:32.125 --> 09:36.333
when there's a lot going on
in my life or, I don't know,
maybe not a lot going on,

09:36.417 --> 09:37.875
I revert to sleepwalking.

09:37.959 --> 09:40.875
You find yourself
in the backyard,

09:40.959 --> 09:42.792
looking for the bathroom.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.333
-Bare-assed.
-(Charlie chuckles)

09:45.417 --> 09:46.917
Now, you're just
trying to distract me.

09:47.000 --> 09:48.083
No.

09:48.166 --> 09:51.083
I smashed into a tree
in the middle of the night

09:51.166 --> 09:53.917
and impaled my arm on a branch.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.917
It hurt like a son of a bitch.

09:56.000 --> 09:59.041
I don't know why I'm laughing.
It wasn't funny.

09:59.834 --> 10:01.417
I don't want you thinking
that if we fall asleep,

10:01.500 --> 10:03.792
I'm gonna go strolling
down the hotel hallway

10:03.875 --> 10:06.000
in my birthday suit.

10:06.083 --> 10:09.417
It might bring some
undue attention to you
hiding out here.

10:09.500 --> 10:11.709
You have a bunch of fun
being a girl, don't you?

10:11.792 --> 10:13.917
Well, I can make
my own decisions,

10:14.000 --> 10:15.417
if that's what you mean.

10:15.500 --> 10:19.417
You mind, uh, if we do it
with the lights off this time?

10:19.500 --> 10:21.583
You tired of looking
at me already?

10:21.667 --> 10:23.041
Oh, no.

10:23.542 --> 10:26.125
I want to fantasize
I'm with you,

10:26.208 --> 10:29.542
and then turn the lights on
and have it come true.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.125
Well, aren't you a poet?

10:33.208 --> 10:36.625
("Save Me" by Nina Simone
playing, muffled)

10:36.709 --> 10:40.125
-(Jett moaning)
-Jesus Christ.

10:40.208 --> 10:43.041
I'm surprised the old ticker
can even take anymore.

10:43.125 --> 10:45.959
Everything's a medicine,
everything's a poison.

10:46.041 --> 10:47.750
What is that,
Indian wisdom?

10:47.834 --> 10:49.875
-I don't know.
I read it once.
-Oh.

10:51.333 --> 10:52.917
Like...

10:53.000 --> 10:55.291
anything you
have-- sugar,

10:55.375 --> 10:57.333
drugs, sex,

10:57.417 --> 11:00.083
it can either all be
a medicine or a poison.

11:00.166 --> 11:04.417
Yep, everything in moderation,
including moderation.

11:04.500 --> 11:05.792
Boom.

11:05.875 --> 11:08.083
You never saw
that one coming.

11:10.208 --> 11:12.250
This is us, brother.

11:12.333 --> 11:13.959
No sirree.

11:14.458 --> 11:15.917
We're not the pawns?

11:16.000 --> 11:18.500
-Back when
I started, maybe.
-Oh.

11:18.583 --> 11:20.750
Now, you're this guy.

11:24.041 --> 11:25.333
You still stalking that chick?

11:25.417 --> 11:27.875
-Not stalking anyone.
-Pardon me.

11:27.959 --> 11:29.917
You still hanging out
outside her apartment all night,

11:30.000 --> 11:31.709
watching her windows?

11:32.417 --> 11:33.875
Check.

11:33.959 --> 11:36.083
How you figure?

11:37.041 --> 11:39.917
Oh, that's not fair.
That's not fair.

11:40.000 --> 11:42.458
You say Arabs
invented this shit?

11:42.542 --> 11:43.667
Out in the desert.

11:43.750 --> 11:46.083
They had all the time
in the world.

11:46.625 --> 11:48.041
See, that's what I don't get.

11:48.125 --> 11:50.000
They got all the time
in the world to figure out

11:50.083 --> 11:51.500
mathematically precise ways
in which

11:51.583 --> 11:52.875
all these other pieces
move, right?

11:52.959 --> 11:55.917
Like, diagonal, L-shape,

11:56.000 --> 11:58.417
up and down,
two steps at a time.

11:58.500 --> 12:00.875
Then they get to the queen.
What, they just get tired?

12:00.959 --> 12:02.166
It's like, fuck it.

12:02.250 --> 12:05.333
This bitch can move whichever
fucking way she likes.

12:06.041 --> 12:08.959
(Jett moaning)

12:09.041 --> 12:11.875
Maybe we should bust in there,
make sure he's all right?

12:12.583 --> 12:14.834
I'm pretty sure
he's better than all right.

12:15.792 --> 12:17.500
Jett:
What about you?

12:18.125 --> 12:20.291
What were you like
when you were a kid?

12:20.834 --> 12:23.542
I remember one year, I tried
to go barefoot year-round.

12:23.625 --> 12:26.041
(chuckles)
I was 13 or 14,

12:26.125 --> 12:28.000
and I was determined to go

12:28.083 --> 12:29.959
year-round without
wearing shoes,

12:30.041 --> 12:31.500
except they wouldn't
let me into church,

12:31.583 --> 12:33.834
and I loved going to church
as a child.

12:34.667 --> 12:37.834
(sighs) I'm a C-minus Christian,
but, you know, I am one.

12:37.917 --> 12:38.875
You?

12:39.500 --> 12:42.750
I don't really believe in all
that cosmic moral accounting.

12:42.834 --> 12:44.458
(chuckles) Then you're lucky.

12:45.000 --> 12:47.583
I wish I could tell you
I didn't buy into it.

12:47.667 --> 12:49.625
(sighs) But I can't shake
some faint awareness

12:49.709 --> 12:51.875
in the back of my mind that

12:51.959 --> 12:55.750
if such a thing as retribution
exists, well (scoffs)...

12:55.834 --> 12:57.291
I damn well deserve it.

12:57.375 --> 12:58.917
What's wrong?

12:59.000 --> 13:00.917
Wrong? Why should
anything be wrong?

13:01.000 --> 13:02.250
The Mexican bedbug again?

13:02.333 --> 13:04.500
Aah, he took a swing at me.

13:05.041 --> 13:06.542
I got to hit him back,

13:06.625 --> 13:09.500
-but that's not what I was
thinking about just then.
-No.

13:09.583 --> 13:11.834
Do you remember
my friend Frank Sweeney?

13:13.166 --> 13:15.333
Sure. Sociopath.

13:15.417 --> 13:17.166
Paul Smith suits.

13:17.250 --> 13:19.375
You worked for him
a couple of times, didn't you?

13:19.458 --> 13:21.083
A long time ago.

13:22.375 --> 13:25.083
Well, he croaked
in his sleep the other night.

13:25.542 --> 13:28.333
I don't know why
it's affecting me so much.

13:28.417 --> 13:32.041
I keep thinking it used to be
I knew a lot of people who died

13:32.125 --> 13:34.166
in the course of doing business.

13:34.250 --> 13:35.667
It comes with the territory.

13:35.750 --> 13:37.750
But lately,
it seems I know

13:37.834 --> 13:39.375
a lot of people
who are dying just 'cause,

13:39.458 --> 13:42.208
well, they're getting old,
and in our line of work,

13:42.291 --> 13:44.625
you can never admit
to getting too old.

13:45.041 --> 13:47.917
Because just saying it,
gives people the wrong idea.

13:48.000 --> 13:49.291
You're not old.

13:49.375 --> 13:51.792
-Not judging by first
responder over there.
-Aah.

13:51.875 --> 13:53.583
That's a sweet thing
to say.

13:54.625 --> 13:57.250
Nobody has ever
called me sweet.

13:57.333 --> 13:59.083
They don't know you
like I do.

13:59.166 --> 14:01.750
-What are you gonna
do about Salas?
-Aah...

14:02.458 --> 14:05.000
Salas is someone
used to power, not brains,

14:05.083 --> 14:07.250
but I can't afford
to wait him out.

14:08.041 --> 14:11.291
He's got a boat full of heroin
docking here next week.

14:14.750 --> 14:16.709
-Can you help me
put this earring back?
-Oh, yeah.

14:16.792 --> 14:18.458
It keeps
falling off.

14:21.750 --> 14:23.834
Yeah, it's a mess
of a setup.

14:23.917 --> 14:26.125
There's only
one exit route.

14:26.959 --> 14:28.542
What would
you do?

14:28.625 --> 14:30.166
Given a choice,
I never go in somewhere

14:30.250 --> 14:32.250
with only one exit route.

14:33.667 --> 14:34.625
Thank you.

14:36.208 --> 14:37.959
Anytime.

14:38.041 --> 14:39.125
(door opens)

14:39.208 --> 14:42.417
(traffic whooshing)

14:57.125 --> 14:59.000
Maria:
How it works,

14:59.083 --> 15:01.709
no one but the doctor can be
with you during labor.

15:01.792 --> 15:04.208
-Jett: No one?
-No.

15:04.291 --> 15:06.875
Maria:
But the guards watch
you on monitors.

15:06.959 --> 15:08.041
Jett:
Sure.

15:08.125 --> 15:09.959
You get 24 hours
with the baby

15:10.041 --> 15:11.208
before they take it away.

15:11.291 --> 15:13.208
They don't want you
forming an attachment.

15:13.291 --> 15:15.375
A social worker takes it,

15:15.458 --> 15:17.542
places it in the system
for adoption.

15:17.625 --> 15:21.834
-What else?
-They handcuff you
right after you give birth,

15:21.917 --> 15:24.458
sometimes even during,
it depends on the prison.

15:24.542 --> 15:26.041
That's it?

